# Application Layer Rules

## Blocs/Cubits
- One Bloc/Cubit per feature
- Keep states immutable
- Use meaningful event/state names
- Handle all possible states

## State Management
- Define clear state classes
- Include loading states
- Handle error states
- Implement proper state transitions

## Event Handling
- Clear event naming
- Document event handlers
- Proper error propagation
- Handle concurrent events

## Dependencies
- Inject dependencies
- Use repository abstractions
- Follow dependency inversion
- Document dependencies

## Error Handling
- Map domain errors to UI errors
- Include user-friendly messages
- Log errors appropriately
- Handle edge cases
